properties.areaDesc: Ferris/Seminoe/Shirley Mountains; North Laramie Range; Shirley Basin
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued March 1 at 9:31PM MST until March 2 at 2:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...PERIODS OF LIGHT TO MODERATE SNOW WITH PATCHY BLOWING SNOW WILL
CONTINUE THROUGH EARLY MONDAY MORNING...

* WHAT...Occasional snow. Additional snow accumulations up to one
inch.

* WHERE...North Laramie Range, Shirley Basin, and northern Carbon
County mountains.

* WHEN...Until 2 AM MST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions and poor driving
conditions.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 2 AM MST MONDAY... ...WINTER STORM WARNING IS CANCELLED
